        <headline>Special Weather Statement issued September 23 at 3:39PM CDT by NWS Little Rock AR</headline>
        <description>At 339 PM CDT, Doppler radar was tracking a strong thunderstorm 7
miles east of Thola, or 11 miles west of Mountain View, moving east
at 20 mph.

HAZARD...Wind gusts of 50 to 55 mph and penny size hail.

SOURCE...Radar indicated.

IMPACT...Gusty winds could knock down tree limbs and blow around
unsecured objects. Minor damage to outdoor objects is
possible.

Locations impacted include...
Mountain View...                  Melbourne...
Brandenberg...                    Lone Star...
Herpel...                         Lunenburg...
Blanchard Springs Campground...   Guion...
Allison...                        Alco...
Hanover...                        Mt Olive in Izard County...
Pleasant Grove...                 Timbo...
Gunner Pool Campground...         Barkshed Campground...
Newnata...                        Luber...
Fifty-Six...                      Boswell...
</description>
        <instruction>If outdoors, consider seeking shelter inside a building.

Torrential rainfall is also occurring with this storm and may lead to
localized flooding. Do not drive your vehicle through flooded
roadways.

A Tornado Watch remains in effect until 1000 PM CDT for north central
Arkansas.</instruction>
